---
import SiteFooter from '../../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import SiteNav from '../../components/SiteNav.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Getting started · neondeck"
  description="Install and run neondeck locally with Node 26, Flue, Kilo, GitHub, and the Astro webapp."
>
  <div class="site-shell">
    <SiteNav />
    <main class="container docs-layout">
      <aside class="docs-sidebar">
        <a href="/docs/">Overview</a>
        <a href="/docs/getting-started/">Getting started</a>
        <a href="#runtime-home">Runtime home</a>
        <a href="#commands">Commands</a>
        <a href="#verify">Verify</a>
      </aside>
      <article class="docs-prose">
        <h1>Getting started</h1>
        <p>
          Use Node 26.4.0 with fnm. The default Flue model is Kilo through the
          custom provider registration in the local backend.
        </p>

        <h2>Install</h2>
        <pre><code>fnm install 26.4.0
fnm use 26.4.0
npm install</code></pre>

        <h2 id="runtime-home">Initialize runtime home</h2>
        <p>
          The app creates a runtime home on first start. You can also prepare it
          explicitly before launching the dashboard.
        </p>
        <pre><code>npm run setup</code></pre>
        <p>
          By default this writes to <code>~/.config/neondeck</code>. Set
          <code>NEONDECK_HOME</code> when you want an isolated test home.
        </p>
        <pre><code>NEONDECK_HOME=.neondeck-test npm run setup</code></pre>

        <h2>Configure secrets</h2>
        <p>
          Copy <code>.env.example</code> to <code>.env</code> and fill in the local
          values.
        </p>
        <pre><code>KILOCODE_API_KEY=...
KILOCODE_ORGANIZATION_ID=...
FLUE_AGENT_MODEL=kilocode/kilo/auto
GITHUB_TOKEN=...
GITHUB_LOGIN=...</code></pre>

        <h2>Run the local dashboard</h2>
        <pre><code>npm run dev</code></pre>
        <p>
          Open <code>http://127.0.0.1:5173/</code> on the companion display.
        </p>

        <h2 id="commands">Run Neon commands</h2>
        <p>
          Commands can be typed into the chat panel or invoked through the
          <code>command-run</code> Flue workflow. Command results are stored as workflow
          summaries for dashboard panels and follow-up agent context.
        </p>
        <pre><code>curl -X POST 'http://127.0.0.1:5173/api/flue/workflows/command-run?wait=result' \
  -H 'content-type: application/json' \
  -d '&#123;"input":&#123;"command":"/briefing"&#125;&#125;'</code></pre>
        <p>Current commands:</p>
        <pre><code>/repo-status [repo-id]
/review-queue
/briefing
/dev-doctor
/watch-pr neondeck#123
/watch-pr neondeck#123 until prod
/watch-release neondeck</code></pre>

        <h2>Configure repositories</h2>
        <p>
          Repositories live in runtime-home <code>repos.json</code>. Neon should
          mutate config through typed actions rather than direct file edits. The
          repo registry powers GitHub PR queues, watches, release checks, local
          repo status, and dev doctor diagnostics.
        </p>

        <h2>Runtime skills</h2>
        <p>
          The built-in Neondeck runtime skill is an application-owned Flue
          skill. User runtime skills load from <code>skills/</code> inside the runtime
          home, plus configured external skill roots, and are registered as Flue skills
          when the agent initializes. Start a new session or restart the server after
          changing runtime skills. Treat runtime skill directories as trusted input
          and do not place secrets in skill resources.
        </p>

        <h2>Agent models</h2>
        <p>
          Configure the display assistant and subagent model choices in
          runtime-home
          <code>config.json</code>. Environment variables remain fallback
          values, but runtime config is the preferred local control point.
        </p>
        <pre><code>&#123;
  "version": 1,
  "models": &#123;
    "displayAssistant": "kilocode/kilo/auto",
    "subagents": &#123;
      "default": "kilocode/kilo/auto",
      "repoResearcher": "kilocode/kilo/auto",
      "ciInvestigator": "kilocode/kilo/auto",
      "releaseReviewer": "kilocode/kilo/auto"
    &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>
        <p>
          The chat agent can update these fields through the typed
          <code>neondeck_config_update_agent_models</code> action. Model strings must
          reference providers already registered by the app or Flue runtime.
        </p>

        <h2 id="verify">Verify locally</h2>
        <pre><code>npm run check
npm run verify</code></pre>
        <p>
          <code>npm run verify</code> runs lint, typecheck, tests, formatting, the
          dashboard build, the Flue Node build, and the Astro webapp build.
        </p>

        <h2>Run the webapp</h2>
        <pre><code>npm run webapp:astro-dev</code></pre>
        <p>
          The Astro marketing/docs site runs separately from the local dashboard
          and deploys to Cloudflare.
        </p>

        <h2>Deploy neondeck.dev</h2>
        <pre><code>npm run webapp:deploy</code></pre>
        <p>
          The Worker is configured in <code>webapp/wrangler.jsonc</code> with custom
          domains for <code>neondeck.dev</code> and <code>www.neondeck.dev</code
          >.
        </p>
      </article>
    </main>
    <SiteFooter />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
